up a burnt gully
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:in phrase look as if one has lived, been up a (the) burnt gully, for the winter; spent the winter up a burnt gully: i.e. to look, or be, very thin, emaciated, underfed (sc.like a sheep which has spent a winter up a burnt off gully where there would be no feed).
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
Citations
Date: 0/0/1963
Source: Half-Gallon Jar
Author: McCALLUM
Vol / Page: 63
Edition:
Quote: The pakeha lady she is nearly always skinny and looks as if she has been up the burnt gully for the winter ... [ibid 72] This coot is about five feet high and very pale. He looks as if he had been living on bird seed or had spent the winter up a burnt gully.
